Description or Content Summary: oral history of Mignone Trouette Conner by interviewer Betsy Kraemer.
Why the recording is significant to Cali: Born in 1908. Long-term resident of Sausalito. Talks about local Sausalito residents: Father Valentine, Mayor Thomas, George Maxwell, Wossers, Fiedlers,  and her grandfather who was constable. and about the gambling era. efforts o clean up the town, Sausalito as a wild place, growth of civic mindedness in the town, the diphtheria epidemic

Description or Content Summary: Oral history of Earl Dunphy by interviewer Chris Hayden
Why the recording is significant to Cali: Long-term resident of Sausalito. Worked for the NWP Railroad and was postmaster in Sausalito. Served as mayor of Sausalito, and was on the city council, planning commission, and coordinator of civilian defense during WWII.  Talks about Marinship Sausalito during WWII.

Description or Content Summary: oral history of Dorothy Gibson by interviewer Betsy Stroman
Why the recording is significant to Cali: Has degree in clinical psychology. Worked at Children's Home Society, an adoption agency and California Dept of Mental Hygiene.Lived in S.F. and now long-term of Sausalito. Talks about Mignone Conner, conflict between business interests and environmentalists, ran for Sausalito  City Council, served on the planning commission.  Wrote Marin Headlands and Exploring Sausalito's Paths and Walkways. Leads walking tours in Sausalito.

Description or Content Summary: Oral Interview of Amy Belser by Barbara Geisler
Why the recording is significant to Cali: Active in Sausalito government: served on City Council, was mayor, served on planning commission, general plan steering committee, Park and Recreation commission and Sausalito Tree Committee.  Also served on Marin County Council of Mayors, League of California Cities Committees, Marin Countrywide Planning Agency and Marin Congestion Management Agency and College of Marin Foundation Board  40+ year resident of Sausalito, active in the community.

Description or Content Summary: oral history of Phil Frank by interviewer Jan Wahl
